{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TuFecNNsf2Zm2yiKMNLHaX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is fully deployed and operational. Here's what was deployed and the two issues encountered:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `ConfigMap/es-config` — elasticsearch.yml with TLS + security config\n- `Service/es-headless` (headless, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) — transport discovery\n- `Service/es-http` (ClusterIP:9200) — HTTPS client access\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/es-pdb` (minAvailable: 2)\n- `StatefulSet/es` (3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, 5Gi PVCs each)\n\n**Two bootstrap issues solved:**\n1. **Deadlock with OrderedReady**: StatefulSet waits for es-0 Ready before starting es-1/es-2, but the readiness probe checks `_cluster/health` which requires a quorum — fixed with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 start simultaneously, plus `timeoutSeconds: 10` on the probe.\n2. **DNS NXDOMAIN for headless service**: Kubernetes only publishes endpoints for Ready pods by default; unready pods can't discover each other — fixed with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service.\n\n**Verified:** cluster is `green` with 3 nodes, document write and read through `es-http` succeed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":642,"cache_read_input_tokens":45542,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":642},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1811e6eb-b38e-40db-9434-e262aa5d8108","uuid":"5fc6d007-6119-4703-b0ec-002f04964ef4","request_id":"req_011CcQRxhMGHN3MfBFenLjUY"}
